d8d2b488-a4b6-4cbf-bf1d-8fcbf761eea6.do_description: To make the output, you have to...make it look like a checkerboard: use the top square provided, the next row will be staggered color, blank, color; the next row will be one square, and so on and so forth to the end. The second colored square represents a new checkerboard design following the same rules. Use the same colors as the starting colored square provided.

d8d2b488-a4b6-4cbf-bf1d-8fcbf761eea6.see_description: In the input, you should see...either one or two colored squares at the top of the grid.
